    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "PS2MS, an AI-powered predictive system designed specifically to address the limitations of identifying the emergence of unidentified novel illicit drugs... When the mass spectrum of an analyte does not match any known reference, PS2MS simultaneously examines the chemical fingerprint and mass spectrum against the putative NPS database using integrated metrics to deduce possible identities.",
      "asbval:note": "The research question directly aligns with the paper's core objective and methodology.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05019",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Can the PS\u00b2MS deep learning system successfully predict and identify new psychoactive substances from mass spectrometry data when applied to test inputs?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:15:26.150971+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we introduce PS2MS, an AI-powered predictive system, designed specifically for this purpose... PS2MS builds a supplementary synthetic NPS database by enumerating possible derivatives based on the core structure of a preselected illicit drug.",
      "asbval:note": "PS2MS is the primary system described throughout the paper and is the subject of the study.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05019",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "PS2MS",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:15:26.150971+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The system subsequently yields a list of potential NPS identities for the analyte... The integrated similarity metric between the analyte and enumerated compounds in the NPS database based on the mass spectrum and fingerprint are calculated, summarized, and ranked.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper produces ranked lists of potential NPS identities with similarity scores (SMSF scores), but does not explicitly describe outputs as a 'table with spectrum identifiers' or use the term 'confidence scores.' The outputs are ranked predictions with similarity metrics rather than explicitly formatted classification tables.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05019",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "NPS classification predictions table with spectrum identifiers, predicted compound classes, and confidence scores per prediction",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:15:26.150971+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card's framing as 'reproduce' predictions suggests running the model on new test data, but the paper primarily validates PS2MS on known cathinone derivatives and real-world eutylone samples. The card does not specify whether it refers to reproducing the paper's validation experiments or applying the system to entirely new unknown substances.",
        "The card's expected output description ('NPS classification predictions table') is somewhat generic and does not capture the paper's specific emphasis on ranking derivatives by SMSF similarity scores and identifying isomers as a key challenge."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 2,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:15:26.150971+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Directed message passing neural networks (D-MPNN18) operate on molecular graphs based on chemical structures in the simplified molecular input line entry system (SMILES19) notation to build neural representations of molecules for property prediction including mass spectra.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper mentions SMILES as a representation format used in related work (D-MPNN), but PS2MS itself uses extended circular fingerprints (ECFPs) and DeepEI for fingerprint generation from mass spectra, not SMILES-to-spectrum encoding. The paper states: 'neural electron\u2013ionization mass spectrometry (NEIMS) utilizes neural networks to convert chemical structure representations (i.e., extended circular fingerprints; ECFPs) into mass spectra'. PS2MS does not directly encode SMILES to mass spectra; instead it uses NEIMS (trained on NIST/SWGDRUG) to predict spectra from enumerated structures, and DeepEI to predict fingerprints from observed spectra.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05019",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How are SMILES representations of NPS chemical structures converted into the encoded feature format required as input for the PS2MS deep learning model?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:15:36.237330+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_002/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "RDKit is not mentioned anywhere in the paper. The paper uses SCScore (neural-network-based synthesis complexity scoring), NEIMS (for mass spectrum prediction), and DeepEI (for fingerprint prediction from spectra). No molecular toolkit like RDKit is explicitly named.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05019",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "RDKit",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:15:36.237330+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_002/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The system leverages two deep learning models, NEIMS and DeepEI, to predict the mass spectrum of the enumerated substances in the NPS database and the structure representations (i.e., fingerprints) of the unidentified analyte, respectively.",
      "asbval:note": "PS2MS does produce feature representations (mass spectra and fingerprints), but the paper does not describe them as NumPy arrays or HDF5 format, nor does it detail the exact shape or encoding pipeline. The paper focuses on NEIMS predicting mass spectra and DeepEI predicting fingerprints, which are then combined via SMSF metric, but does not describe a 'SMILES-to-encoded-features' module as the card implies.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05019",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Encoded feature matrix (NumPy array or HDF5 format) with shape [n_compounds, n_features] ready for PS2MS model input",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:15:36.237330+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card frames the task as reconstructing a 'SMILES-to-mass-spectrum feature encoding module', but PS2MS does not perform direct SMILES-to-spectrum encoding. Instead, it: (1) enumerates derivatives from a template structure, (2) uses NEIMS to predict mass spectra from those enumerated structures, and (3) uses DeepEI to infer fingerprints from observed spectra of unknowns. The encoding direction is reversed for unknowns (spectrum \u2192 fingerprint via DeepEI).",
        "The card's focus on SMILES representation is not central to PS2MS's workflow. PS2MS uses structural enumeration via functional group replacement and filtering (SCScore, drug-like rules), not SMILES parsing or RDKit-based feature extraction.",
        "The card implies a single 'feature encoding module' that converts SMILES to a matrix format, but PS2MS uses two separate deep learning models (NEIMS and DeepEI) for different purposes and does not describe a unified encoding pipeline."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:15:36.237330+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_003/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "PS2MS employs the SMSF (integrated similarity metric based on mass spectrum and fingerprint) to prioritize derivatives... The system subsequently yields a list of potential NPS identities for the analyte",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does evaluate PS2MS prediction scores (SMSF metric) across different compound types (cathinone vs. noncathinone, isomers, real-world samples). However, the paper does NOT explicitly stratify analysis by 'structural novelty category' as a primary variable. The paper evaluates performance on known cathinones, noncathinones, and isomers, but does not systematically categorize or analyze structural novelty as an independent variable with stratified confidence metrics.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05019",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How do prediction confidence scores from the PS2MS deep learning model vary across structurally diverse or novel NPS analogues in the evaluation dataset?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:15:51.532367+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_003/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper reports SMSF scores and performance metrics (sensitivity, specificity, F1 score, ranking proportions) but does not provide stratified statistical summaries (mean, median, std, quartiles) organized by structural novelty categories. The paper presents individual scores and ranking distributions but not aggregated descriptive statistics stratified by novelty.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05019",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Table of prediction confidence score statistics (mean, median, std, min, max, quartiles) stratified by structural novelty category",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:15:51.532367+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_003/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper provides histograms, scatter plots, and ranking proportion curves (Figures 3, 4, 5) but does not present box plots or violin plots stratified by structural novelty categories. Visualizations focus on ranking performance and similarity score distributions for specific compounds (e.g., \u03b1-PPP, 4-EMC, Eutylone) rather than novelty-stratified distributions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05019",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Visualization (box plot or violin plot) of confidence score distributions across structural novelty strata",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:15:51.532367+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1021_acs_analchem_3c05019__task_003/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The system leverages two deep learning models, NEIMS and DeepEI, to predict the mass spectrum of the enumerated substances in the NPS database and the structure representations (i.e., fingerprints) of the unidentified analyte, respectively.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses deep learning models (NEIMS, DeepEI) but does not explicitly name PyTorch or TensorFlow as the implementation framework. The underlying framework for these models is not disclosed in the passages provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05019",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
