    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chemical-structure-featurization/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The system leverages two deep learning models, NEIMS and DeepEI, to predict the mass spectrum of the enumerated substances in the NPS database and the structure representations (i.e., fingerprints) of the unidentified analyte, respectively.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses SMILES notation and deep learning for fingerprint/spectrum prediction, but does NOT explicitly describe converting SMILES to 'fixed-size numerical feature tensors' as a standalone task. The paper mentions SMILES as input format but focuses on the downstream models (NEIMS, DeepEI) rather than the featurization step itself. The card frames featurization as a primary skill; the paper treats it as implicit infrastructure.",
