    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/molecular-descriptor-extraction/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The system leverages two deep learning models, NEIMS and DeepEI, to predict the mass spectrum of the enumerated substances in the NPS database and the structure representations (i.e., fingerprints) of the unidentified analyte, respectively.",
      "asbval:note": "PS2MS does use deep learning models (NEIMS, DeepEI) that require numerical input, but the paper does not describe converting SMILES to fixed-size tensors. Instead, NEIMS takes ECFPs (extended circular fingerprints) as input (passage 3: 'extended circular fingerprints; ECFPs'), and DeepEI converts mass spectra to fingerprints. The actual input format and tensor construction are not detailed in the passages provided.",
