      "asbval:note": "Paper uses fingerprints for similarity-based matching and ranking of derivatives, but does NOT perform stratification by structural novelty relative to training data, nor does it aggregate confidence scores by novelty stratum. The paper evaluates performance on known cathinones vs. noncathinones and real-world samples, but not via the proposed stratification-by-training-distance methodology. The research question describes a novel analytical approach not demonstrated in the paper.",
