    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tensor-encoding-deep-learning/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The system leverages two deep learning models, NEIMS and DeepEI, to predict the mass spectrum of the enumerated substances in the NPS database and the structure representations (i.e., fingerprints) of the unidentified analyte, respectively.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses SMILES and molecular structures as inputs to deep learning models (NEIMS, DeepEI), but does not explicitly describe a 'tensor encoding' step. The paper mentions 'extended circular fingerprints (ECFPs)' and 'simplified molecular input line entry system (SMILES)' as chemical structure representations fed to neural networks, but the specific tensor encoding process is not detailed in the passages provided. The functional goal (converting structures to neural network inputs) is present, but the explicit 'tensor encoding' methodology is not described.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-3c05019",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tensor-encoding-deep-learning",
