    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tensor-encoding-deep-learning/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The system leverages two deep learning models, NEIMS and DeepEI, to predict the mass spectrum of the enumerated substances in the NPS database... neural networks to convert chemical structure representations (i.e., extended circular fingerprints; ECFPs) into mass spectra",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms NEIMS and DeepEI are used for mass spectrum and fingerprint prediction from chemical structures. However, the paper does not explicitly state that RDKit is used to create SMILES or molecule objects, nor does it detail the tensor encoding step. The paper mentions ECFPs as structure representations but does not describe how SMILES \u2192 tensor conversion occurs.",
